casebody.data:
The UNION NATIONAL BANK OF YOUNGSTOWN, Appellant, v. Carl E. MOORE, Collector of Internal Revenue, Appellee. No. 8166. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. June 28, 1939. Manchester, Ford & Powers, of Youngstown, Ohio, for appellant. E. B. Freed, U. S. Atty., and E. L. Foote, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Cleveland, Ohio, for appellee.

Before HICKS, ALLEN, and HAMILTON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal herein be and the same is dismissed pursuant to motion of appellant.
